//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of artifacts sharing a common
{rbtga_hallmark}
but distinguished by suffix.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(`-image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(`-about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(`-vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(`-pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth artifact, `-diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
Abjuring an ark removes all existing artifacts as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if vessel missing: "Vessel parameter required"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Registry Endpoint*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_HOST»` as `{rbrr_gcp_region}-docker.pkg.dev`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_PATH»` as `{rbrr_depot_project_id}/{rbrr_gar_repository}`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_BASE»` as `https://«REGISTRY_HOST»/v2/«REGISTRY_PATH»`

//axhos_step
. *Construct Ark Tags*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-image`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ABOUT_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-about`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VOUCH_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-vouch`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«POUCH_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-pouch`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIAGS_TAG»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-diags`
.. If vessel mode is conjure:
... For each platform in `RBRV_CONJURE_PLATFORMS`:
.... Derive `«ARCH_SUFFIX»` from platform (e.g., `linux/amd64` → `amd64`, `linux/arm/v7` → `armv7`)
.... {rbbc_store}
`«ATTEST_TAG_n»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL»:«INPUT_HALLMARK»-attest-«ARCH_SUFFIX»`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Ark Existence*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#pulling-manifests[Docker Registry API: HEAD manifests] for `«IMAGE_TAG»`:
... method: `HEAD`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-image`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... header: `Accept: application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json, application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json, application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json, application/vnd.oci.image.manifest.v1+json`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404
.. {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request for `«ABOUT_TAG»`:
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-about`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ABOUT_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404
.. {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request for `«VOUCH_TAG»`:
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-vouch`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VOUCH_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404
.. {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request for `«POUCH_TAG»`:
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-pouch`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«POUCH_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404 (optional — conjure/bind only, absent for graft)
.. {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request for `«DIAGS_TAG»`:
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-diags`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIAGS_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404 (optional — conjure-only, absent for bind/graft)
.. If `«ATTEST_TAG_n»` tags were constructed (conjure vessels):
... For each `«ATTEST_TAG_n»`:
.... {rbbc_call}
same HEAD request:
..... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-attest-«ARCH_SUFFIX»`
.... {rbbc_store}
`«ATTEST_n_EXISTS»` as true if HTTP 200, false if HTTP 404

//axhos_step
. *Evaluate Ark State*:
.. If all of `«IMAGE_EXISTS»`, `«ABOUT_EXISTS»`, and `«VOUCH_EXISTS»` are false:
... {rbbc_fatal}
"Ark not found: no artifacts exist"
.. If exactly one exists:
... {rbbc_warn}
"Orphaned artifact detected"
... {rbbc_show}
which artifact exists and which is missing
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARTIFACTS_TO_DELETE»` as list of existing artifacts

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. Unless `--force` flag provided:
... {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure ark «INPUT_VESSEL»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»:" followed by each artifact in `«ARTIFACTS_TO_DELETE»`
... {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
... {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Image Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«IMAGE_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-image`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -image artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete About Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«ABOUT_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-about`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -about artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete Vouch Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«VOUCH_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-vouch`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -vouch artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete Pouch Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«POUCH_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-pouch`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -pouch artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete Diags Artifact* (if exists):
.. If `«DIAGS_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-diags`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -diags artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhos_step
. *Delete Attest Artifacts* (conjure vessels, if exist):
.. For each `«ATTEST_TAG_n»` where `«ATTEST_n_EXISTS»`:
... {rbbc_call}
Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«INPUT_VESSEL»/manifests/«INPUT_HALLMARK»-attest-«ARCH_SUFFIX»`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete -attest-«ARCH_SUFFIX» artifact (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Ark abjured: «INPUT_VESSEL»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»"
.. For each deleted artifact:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «TAG» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when all existing ark artifacts have been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`hallmarks/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SUBTREE»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/` where `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` derives from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled from `RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX` + `hallmarks`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARK_PACKAGES»` as the list of decoded package names whose prefix equals `«SUBTREE»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«ARK_PACKAGES»` is empty: "No packages found under «SUBTREE» — hallmark not present in registry"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. Unless `--force` flag provided:
... {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure «COUNT» packages under «SUBTREE»:" followed by each entry in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`
... {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
... {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Each Enumerated Package*:
.. For each `«PACKAGE»` in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ENCODED»` as `«PACKAGE»` with `/` replaced by `%2F`
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/delete[GAR REST API: packages.delete] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages/«ENCODED»`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response (deletion returns a long-running operation; the 200 is treated as accepted)
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete package «PACKAGE» (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Hallmark abjured: «INPUT_HALLMARK» («COUNT» packages)"
.. For each deleted package:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «PACKAGE» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree has been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.
Because enumeration drives the delete set, there is no separate existence check and no orphan-detection branch: whatever lives in the subtree is removed, and an empty subtree is itself the "not present" signal.
Deleting a package removes all of its tags in one call — per-basename HEAD/DELETE dances are no longer required.

