//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_graft}

NOTE: This operation grafts a locally-built container image into
{rbtgi_repository}
via native docker/podman push.
No Cloud Build involvement in the image push — the image is already built on the local workstation.
No crane dependency — docker tag + docker push is sufficient for locally-present images.
No dirty-tree guard — git state is irrelevant to an already-built container.

NOTE: The name "graft" comes from botanical grafting — foreign material spliced onto rootstock.
The graft may take or may not.
The metaphor fits the trust posture: grafted images have no provenance chain and receive a GRAFTED verdict from
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}.

NOTE: Graft uses whatever container runtime the `docker` command resolves to in PATH, matching other {rbtr_director}-side operations.
No separate regime variable governs runtime selection for graft.

The
{rbtr_director}
grafts an image:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
local image reference provided as second argument (or defaulted from {rbrv_graft_image})
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel mode is {rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source vessel configuration from `rbrv.env`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` from {rbrv_vessel_mode}
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_MODE»` is `graft`

//axhos_step
. *Verify Local Image Exists*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker image inspect «LOCAL_IMAGE_REF»` (or podman equivalent)
.. {rbbc_require}
image exists in local container runtime
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_DIGEST»` from local image inspect
.. {rbbc_store}
`«LOCAL_PLATFORMS»` from local image manifest (typically single-platform for local builds)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark*:
.. {rbbc_call}
query local container runtime for image creation timestamp via `docker image inspect` (the `Created` field — OCI Image Configuration spec, exposed at `.Created` by both docker and podman)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«IMAGE_CREATED»` as the image's creation timestamp, converted to `YYMMDDHHMMSS` format
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»` as current UTC time (`YYMMDDHHMMSS`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«HALLMARK»` as `g«IMAGE_CREATED»-r«PUSH_TIMESTAMP»`
.. T1 encodes when the image was created (a fact about the artifact); T2 encodes when it was pushed to GAR
.. NOTE: The `created` field may be `1970-01-01T00:00:00Z` for reproducible builds. This produces `g700101000000-r...` — a true statement about the image, not an error.

//axhos_step
. *Tag and Push Image*:
.. {rbbc_call}
`docker login` to GAR registry with director credentials
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REGISTRY_TAG»` as `«GAR_HOST»/«GAR_PATH»/hallmarks/«HALLMARK»/image:«HALLMARK»`
